.TH REVERT-OKD-PERMISSIONS 1 "2026-05-22" "SCD Reporting v0.1.0" "SCD Reporting"
.SH NAME
revert-okd-permissions \- restore standard file permissions in the Dockerfile after OKD patching
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./scripts/revert-okd-permissions.sh
[\fIDOCKERFILE\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B revert-okd-permissions.sh
is the inverse of
.BR update-okd-permissions (1).
It restores the Dockerfile to the standard (non-OpenShift) permission
pattern where the runtime user owns
.I /app
outright:
.PP
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Removes
.B \-\-gid 0
from the
.B useradd
call.
.IP \(bu 2
Replaces
.B "chgrp -R 0 /app && chmod -R g=u /app"
with
.B "chown -R appuser:appuser /app"
.RE
.PP
The script is idempotent: if the standard pattern is already present it
exits without making changes.
A timestamped backup is written to
.B $TMPDIR
before any modifications.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I DOCKERFILE
Path to the Dockerfile to restore.
.br
Default:
.B docker/web/Dockerfile
(relative to the repository root).
.SH EXAMPLES
Restore the default Dockerfile:
.PP
.RS
.EX
./scripts/revert-okd-permissions.sh
.EE
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR update-okd-permissions (1),
.BR build-docker (1)
